&lt;p&gt;President Donald Trump on Tuesday reimposed a naval blockade on all Iranian ports and warned that the United States would target Iran&amp;rsquo;s power plants and bridges next week unless Tehran agrees to resume negotiations, marking the latest escalation in the conflict between the two countries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The United States also launched a fresh wave of strikes aimed at &quot;continuing to degrade Iranian capabilities used to attack commercial shipping in the Strait of Hormuz,&quot; the US military said.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tehran said it had once again closed the Strait of Hormuz after fighting between Iran and the United States reignited last week, further undermining a fragile truce reached in June following months of conflict that has claimed thousands of lives.&lt;/p&gt;
